open new terminal run these:
ros2 launch turtlebot4_navigation slam.launch.py
ros2 launch turtlebot4_navigation localization.launch.py map:=office_map.yaml
ros2 launch turtlebot4_navigation nav2.launch.py
ros2 launch turtlebot4_viz view_robot.launch.py
after run python code:
cd turtlebot4_ws
ros2 run turtlebot4_python_tutorials turtlebot4_first_python_node

source install/local_setup.bash
colcon build --symlink-install
ros2 topic echo /clicked_point

manual tf transform:
ros2 run tf2_ros static_transform_publisher 0 0 0 1.571 0 0 base_link wheel_drop_left
(according to ros2 run rqt_tf_tree rqt_tf_tree we can see that all are part of odom but i added them to map instead of odom only the part of wheels)

to know the position of this point after publish:
ros2 topic echo /clicked_point

ros2 run rqt_console rqt_console

ros2 topic echo /odom

https://get-help.theconstruct.ai/t/solved-ros2-subscriber-callback-not-working/19297/4

https://github.com/roboticvedant/ROS2_turtlesim_PID_demo/blob/main/src/turtle_demo_controller/turtle_demo_controller/turtle_controller_with_pid_implimentation.py   (PID TURTLESIM PYTHON CODE)

ros2 param set /amcl update_min_d -1.0
ros2 param set /amcl update_min_a -1.0

ros2 param get /amcl update_min_d
ros2 param get /amcl update_min_a

ros2 topic info /amcl_pose
ros2 topic echo /cmd_vel

ros2 run rqt_reconfigure rqt_reconfigure
